2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 126
BY SENATOR BARROW
A RESOLUTION
To recognize Friday, May 22, 2026, as World Preeclampsia Awareness Day in the state of
Louisiana and to commend Woman's Hospital for its dedication to lifesaving care for
pregnant women, helping to reduce preventable maternal and infant deaths and
reducing the number of preterm births.
WHEREAS, May is recognized nationally and internationally as Preeclampsia
Awareness Month, dedicated to increasing understanding of this life-threatening
hypertensive disorder of pregnancy; and
WHEREAS, World Preeclampsia Day is observed annually on May 22, to raise
global awareness of preeclampsia, a serious pregnancy related condition that poses
significant risks to maternal and infant health; and
WHEREAS, preeclampsia is most often characterized by a rapid rise in blood
pressure that can lead to seizure, stroke, multiple organ failure, and the death of the mother,
baby, or both; and
WHEREAS, the United States currently ranks forty-seventh worldwide for maternal
mortality and is the only industrialized nation with a rising maternal mortality rate; and
WHEREAS, in the United States, preeclampsia complicates approximately one in
every twenty-five pregnancies; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana recorded a maternal mortality rate of 41.9 deaths per
one hundred thousand live births, the highest in the nation; and
WHEREAS, according to America's Health Rankings, approximately eighteen
percent of Louisiana women ages eighteen to forty-four have been told by a healthcare
professional that they have high blood pressure, placing Louisiana forty-sixth among all
states; and
WHEREAS, sixty percent of hypertension-related maternal deaths are considered
potentially preventable with timely diagnosis, treatment, and coordinated care; and
WHEREAS, maternal death has profound and lasting emotional, social, and
economic impacts on families and communities throughout Louisiana; and
