WHEREAS, the primary treatment for preeclampsia involves early delivery of the
infant to prevent disease progression and complications; and
WHEREAS, in 2024, Louisiana ranked fifty-first among the fifty states and Puerto
Rico for preterm births, with preeclampsia being a significant contributing factor; and
WHEREAS, Louisiana continues to rank among the states with the highest infant
mortality rates in the United States, with 9.0 deaths per one thousand live births compared
to the national average of 5.6, according to America's Health Rankings.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby recognize Friday, May 22, 2026, as World Preeclampsia Awareness Day in the
state of Louisiana and does hereby commend Woman's Hospital for its dedication to
life-saving care for pregnant women, helping to reduce preventable maternal and infant
deaths and reducing the number of preterm births.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Rene
Ragas, FACHE, President and Chief Executive Officer of Woman's Hospital.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
